title: Great Location
text: We stayed on a powered waterfront site, it is a short walk to town and unlike staying right in the town do do not tend to get the really high winds They keep the pet area away from the sites without pets which is also really good. Can get a little noisy early morning but you should be up and moving anyways.

title: Great park
text: Just enjoyed our 10 days at this very clean park - Rob was fantastic getting us parked up. Very busy over the weekends but we certainly will return. We did not want to leave today as we felt we were just starting to settle in.

title: Good chinese restaurant
text: Good old fashioned chinese - it is exactly what it sounds like not a top restaurant but good for what it is
place: The Bistro at Tewantin Noosa Bowls Club

title: Great day
text: Really enjoyed our day staff were really nice food was good not fantastic but it is the whole experience that you pay for

title: Good cocktails with nice music
text: We went twice during our stay there was music both times and we will return it is pleasant sitting near the water

title: Very good food
text:
This little restaurant had great food the service was a little ordinary but they could have been training the young girl.

Would return

title: Food is Fantastic
text:
We were the only diners so early in the evening so no worries about social distancing.
The owner and cook came and talked to us about his plans very interesting
People of Laurieton visit this Indian although we did not order a lot of food it was fresh and very tasty. It was perfect Indian. Cannot wait for our next trip to Laurieton.

title: Wow cleanest chinese ever
text:
This restaurant has the COVID restrictions down pat.
Truly impressed with measures and how clean everything was.
It makes you feel comfortable straight away.
Food - we had the lunch specials great size and quite tasty not fantastic but for the cost and the comfort will def return

title: Great spot but a downside
text:
This is a fantastic spot for a caravan park - right on the river with great fishing from the boat ramp and sensational views.
It is a long walk to the amenities seems a little odd where they are.
On the flip side these amenities are dated but spotless.
Sadly there had been a lot of rain just before our visit so the ground was cold and wet also being winter there was very little sunshine as the park is very tree lined which would be fantastic in summer but made it quite cool
In saying all this we would return but in summer it is close to town and beaches fishing and hiking

title: Average meal in beautiful setting
text:
Great social distancing set up -
Food was typical pub fare and was very good for what it was
Fantastic views will return

title: Very good
text:
Great - first walk in everything in place for COVID
Food very good all 4 diners very happy and enjoyed our meals would recommend

title: At odds with this restaurant
text:
We booked a table for 4 to begin no sign in for COVID, then they wanted us to sit in a small table right in the doorway where everyone would be walking past closely. They did have one other table near the wall which we took. Thanks for the change that was appreciated.
The food was good, only one of us loved it the other 3 thought it was good but not great.
Service was fantastic, but overall we were uncomfortable with how close the seating seemed to be.

title: Great service
text: Even though we were unable to go to Hat Head due to COVID 19 as we live in QLD they refunded our money which was fantastic we really appreciated this as we have so many credits and probably will not be able to use them

title: Not as good as we were told
text: People were raving about this restaurant we found our pizza tasty and fresh - service was ordinary so think it was hit and miss

title: Good food
text: Good food in an upmarket setting service was quick and very pleasant we will return next time we are in the gegion

title: Great location
text:
Great location easy walk to restaurants the hall of fame is next door, amenities are clean and neat - we travelled for a golf trip and on our day off they brought us scones jam and cream for morning tea such a nice touch.
We stayed 9 nights and will be back

title: Great burger
text: We didn't start well - we ordered some margarita's and they were truly awful- we settled on other drinks and the manger then made a margarita for us to try and it was good. Thanks. The burger was fresh and very good

title: Birthday Dinner
text: We went for hubby's birthday it really was excellent food hubby had a steak which he said was perfect I had a seafood curry also amazing . they gave him a bottle of bubbles which was a lovely touch and appreciated we will recommend to friends in the area and travellers like us

title: Wonderful cheeses
text: We tasted their fetta at Moothi Vineyard and had to go straight there beautiful cheeses - we purchased way too much but they are amazing

title: Great Lunch with fantastic views
text: What a great find= amazing little vineyard with fantastic views - we had a ploughmans lunch which was all local just lovely - not a lot of white wines just a chardy and a reisling both were nice

title: Good meal
text: Great lunch very basic for us - wanted to go back for a dinner whilst in town but ran out of time the steaks looked amazing and the have a drying chamber- will have to wait till next time - can't wait

title: Great tasting
text: We didn't have a meal here but a beer tasting and some wine. The beers were good lovely ambience staff really friendly next time in Mudgee we will be back

title: Great lunch
text: We stopped in for lunch the food was great huge size at a very reasonable price the staff very friendly and the place was clean

title: Lots of workers so pretty nosiy
text: Great amenities the showers are good that is a positive -but there are a lot of workers in the cabins this is great for the park but it is really noisy with the trucks from around 6.30 and also in the afternoon early evening. If is convenient to town and the local golf course I have to say the girl at reception really didn't care at check in , In saying this there is nothing wrong with the sites and the park is very clean and well cared for - will we stay there again Yes

title: Great display
text: make sure you also do the 3D show very informative, we really enjoyed our time at the dish a good 30 minutes out of town but an easy drive

title: All the little touches count
text: Yes I agree with another review that the levelling of the van was an issue, but they supplied some extra chocks which really helped. What we loved was the little touches soap and water at the dump site, bath mats supplied if needed we use our own but great if needed amenties spotless, a bit dated but that does not matter when they are clean Lisa and Leanne were always around and were very efficient,

title: Good food and service
text: good food and service but no views , on a very busy road looked all closed up but once we found the entrance we enjoyed our time there

title: Lovely views
text: What a lovely little restaurant with great views good food and really nice local wines we enjoyed our lunch here very much
place: Boiler House Restaurant at Hotel Majestic

title: Old world charm
text: What views what glamour, usually old hotels like this are faded and run down not this one stunning upkeep- we did not stay overnight but we will now just beautiful can't wait to return. High tea cocktails elegance and views it has it all

title: Great meal
text: Great food, great prices good size portions, BYO the wait staff were very nice also we would return next trip to the mountains

title: Be early
text: You have to be early on a Fri or Sat the best thing was the service the staff were very good - as a group of 4 we had 2 good meals and 2 very ordinary meals

title: Good food
text: The food is good but not great - service was very good - a large restaurant at the end of Katoomba St,

title: Always great to see water
text: Yes there are falls everywhere up here and this is just another it is close to echo point and the 3 sisters

title: Amazing
text: This is the highlight of The Blue Mountains just beautiful at different times of the day the colours change and you are always captivated

title: Beautiful
text: You can never tire of looking at this stunning scenery there seemed to be a lot of european travellers here at this time

title: Stunning
text: There is fire damage in some areas and a few houses burnt down but the majority of the region is in the usual pristine condition

title: Busy little park in great location
text: This park is close to town across the road from the walks to The 3 sisters and echo point - amenities clean, owners seem nice found it a little noisy but you can't help that travellers from overseas don't really care. Found the town so very busy hard to get parks the fires and floods do not seem to have affected this area at all

title: Good food
text: Good food, good prices although not an extensive menu - servers do not speak great english but that is not really a problem - give it a try

title: lovely location
text: We have a lakeview site that seems that the slab is fairly new - it is fantastic the esign is great plenty of space you can have an extra car or a boat- truly we are sick of being jammed on small sites with on room for your car this is a joy we will be telling others and will return again - the amenities are clean you are surrounded by water and it would be great for the boatie, families, surfers kayakers you seem to have it all. Make the effort and have a stay

title: Very good food
text: The staff and owner was stressed when we got there due to people coming early it did not worry us at all, the food was fresh, served in a timely manner and very tasty we had no complaints, we will see you next time we are passing through

title: Service very slow
text: The food was fine but they took forever to take our order which maybe they were understaffed on the night but they seen us standing there for a long time and could have just called out be there soon - anyway the food was good but no means great

title: Great views and locations
text: Nice owner, manager- clean site well maintained very clean amenties- excellent camps kitchen, some of the best cabins I have seen ( we did not stay in them) we had a powered site with nice views although a main road runs along the back it was peaceful good walking tracks to the beach. close to Laurieton and not that far from Lake Dathie and Port Macquarie if you want the rat race. Will be back

title: Excellent meal
text: Fantastic birthday meal for 8 loved the food and the service was pretty good too. Great outlook overlooking one our this country's premier golf courses

title: Spectacular
text: We have stayed here and played here previously but...this time it is hard to fault we were there for my sons 40th birthday the course was in pristine condition there was nothing to fault- the womens professional was starting 10 days later so this is a given I guess, the rooms were good Highlight was the food it is never cheap but it was fantastic sevice was very good also. Looking forward to our next trip.

title: Great find
text: What a great little restaurant, good food and plenty of it great prices, good wine nice service and a young man playing a guitar and singing maybe a tad loud but he had a lovely voice. Will return and recommend

title: Fantastic meal but pricey
text: We had the degustation 8 course meal at $180pp it was fantastic, we went for our 42nd wedding anniversary so our meal cost 260 and then 1 bottle of wine, water and 2 glasses of bubbles was another 180 plus the tip. In fairness the meal was fantastic the service was amazing happy to pay for the food but thought the drinks where overprices especially a glass of bubbles at 35. Loved the night not where we would go regularly but for a special night great.

title: Great restaurant
text: Lovely chinese restaurant we went to for lunch food was fresh and tasty we enjoyed it very much and would return

title: Mixed feelings
text: Firstly, what a great location. We had a site on the beach side the first site they alloted us was very tight we had to go into the garden to get in - not a great start once in the people before us had emptied their waste into the gravel there were flys and garbabe yuck. So we wanted to move. No problem after being told we will throw some bleach on it- we don't care we want to move. which we did from them on it was fantastic great location, clean amenities although dated. just pretty tight.

title: Almost the same level as Mollymook
text: We enjoyed our meal, the service was great, food very good great wine selection , staff attentive - another hit -a bit out of the way
place: Rick Stein at Bannisters Port Stephens

title: Small sites
text: The location of this park is good, we had a ensuite site which was very tight with a van over 8,5 metres. Our biggest thing was we were on the main entry road and the kids were everywhere even though it was not school holiday this is not the parks fault but I walked beside our car on entry and exit to watch for kids running out from behind cars

title: Some good some bad
text: Start with the bad, we rang up prior to our booking to see if we could get in early .. we couldn't no problem but they said come early in the morning and we will fit you in. We arrived just before 11 and the girl said we could not get on a site yet please wait... this is a little problem as there was markets on that day the road was so full we pull a big van so can't turn around we just sit there, also no great problem as they stated it was full the night prior. Anyway no one way coming out so hubby went over to see how long we had to wait this is after about 40 mins, yes now you can come in. We get to our allotted spacious site the park is half empty and this is why we loved it there was so much space and they didn't put everyone close to one another it was fantastic. The amenities are clean and modern a very family friendly park but as it was not school holiday fine for us. Location is fantastic. We will return not in the holidays though. Thing at check in just odd.

title: Excellent Park
text: We have enjoyed out stay at the Big 4 park in Sawtell, efficient check in , Good size sites, very clean amenities although I found the washing machine pretty dirty, right near the beach, Park is well maintained we will return.

title: huge snack meal
text: We shared a snack or special of the day after a round of golf on this beautiful course. It was more than enough for the 2 of us tasty and fresh the staff were very nice also.
place: The Tee Off Seafood& Steak Bistro

title: The club is good restaurant is OK
text: We have gone to the club a couple of time over our week in Sawtell we have enjoyed it both times. The club is clean the staff are really nice. We ate at the Chinese restaurant one night and just found it good not great but in saying that would try it again next time.

title: Too late for lunch
text: We were just a little late for lunch so got a meal from the snack bar to be honest it was a hamburger that we shared it came very quickly the staff were very nice and the burger was very good for a burger.

title: Great pub meal
text: We had lunch here the restaurant is very clean, the kitchen looks very clean modern setting, and the menu is based around seafood and local fish which is great, we really enjoyed our meal

title: Good food
text: We found this restaurant to have good Indian food, fresh and clean good prices staff were very good, But, food was good not great

title: Great meal
text: Very good meal, great drinks, good prices and the service was very good. We will return next time we are in town again

title: Average chinese
text: Clean neat country chinese, found the meal average, the service was pretty good and the meal came out qquickly would not return in truth would try somewhere else

title: Great country park
text: Just one night in this clean neat country park amenities are basic but clean, we would stay again. Staff were very plesant and efficient there is a pool, the sites are a good size and they space the travellers out a bit.
